cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper discusses the implementation of a GPS-based vehicle tracking system on a system-on-chip (SOC) built on a field programmable gate array (FPGA), which is a typical topic in the embedded systems field.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes different designs and hardware implementations for the SOC, which involves the architecture of the system.
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper mentions the use of GPS technology, which involves the study of electromagnetic waves and their propagation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the performance analysis and evaluation of the proposed designs, which is related to the control and optimization of the system.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): Although not the main focus of the paper, the implementation of a GPS-based vehicle tracking system involves the use of data structures and algorithms for processing and analyzing the data.
